title: The manuscripts of His Grace the Duke of Portland, preserved at Welbeck abbey ...
snippet: It is about fourtofin miles from Tlouf^hton to Lynn. We came there about half an hour past nine o'clock, to the " Duke's Head," a very lar^e house upon the market place, very civil people, kept by Mr. Robert Chennery. The house belongs to one Mr. .John Turner, as also a large house which was his dwelling house over against this inn.

title: England from a Back-Window; with views of Scotland and Ireland
author: Bailey, James Montgomery.
snippet: Presently we ambled on to a paved square, across it to a frowning-looking structure, and were set down in front of an archway, down whose court shone a light from a many-paned window. And this was the Duke's Head.

title: The manuscripts of His Grace the Duke of Portland, preserved at Welbeck abbey ...
